quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  11,118,"And had your Lord willed, He would have made mankind one nation – and they will always keep differing."
  11,119,"Except those upon whom your Lord had mercy; and this is why He created them; and the Word of your Lord has been concluded that, “Indeed I will, surely, fill hell with jinns and men combined.”"
  11,120,"And We relate to you all the accounts of Noble Messengers, in order to steady your heart with it; and in this the truth has come to you, and for the Muslims a preaching and advice."
  11,121,"And say to the disbelievers, “Keep on with your works in your places; we are carrying out ours.”"
  11,122,"“And wait – we too are waiting.”"
  11,123,"“And for Allah only are the hidden of the heavens and of the earth, and towards Him only is the return of all matters – therefore worship Him and trust Him; and your Lord is not unaware of what you do.”"
  12,1,"Alif-Lam-Ra*; these are verses of the clear Book. (* Alphabets of the Arabic language; Allah and to whomever He reveals, know their precise meanings.)"
  12,2,"Indeed We have sent down an Arabic Qur’an, so that you may perceive."
  12,3,"We relate to you the best narrative because We have sent the divine revelation of this Qur’an, to you; although surely you were unaware before this."
  12,4,"Remember when Yusuf (Joseph) said to his father, “O my father! I saw eleven stars and the sun and the moon – I saw them prostrating to me.”"
